    "35050970": {
      "title": "Complement-mediated hemolysis in agar gel",
      "abstract": "Anti-sheep hemolysins of rabbit and human origin formed circular zones of hemolysis when they were diffusing into agar containing sheep erythrocytes and complement. These zones could be reduced in size by allowing antisera with hetero- or isoantibodies for γG-globulins to diffuse against the hemolysins. The practical application of hemolysis in agar gel was explored in studying lysis of bovine erythrocytes by infectious mononucleosis sera and lysis of human erythrocytes by the hemolytic variety of human anti-A and anti-B antibodies."
